cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is about the convergence analysis of adaptive gradient methods in deep learning, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since these fields heavily rely on optimization techniques. The paper also discusses the empirical results of deep learning, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of stochastic gradients, which could be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
